    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-03-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-03-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/3–2351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting Chairman of the United States Delegation to the Torquay
                        Conference</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corse</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d486fn1">Repeated to London as 4335.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-03-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 23, 1951—7 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>507. <gloss target="#t_USTAC1">USTAC</gloss>.</p>
                <p>1. Package deal with Canad (<gloss target="#t_Deltel1">Deltel</gloss> 552 Mar 17)
                    approved by Pres today Mar 23. Deal recommended to Pres with only Agri
                    dissenting because inclusion offer Cheddar cheese.</p>
                <p>2. Pres’ approval covered (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) all items specified annex
                    referred to in <gloss target="#t_Deltel1">Deltel</gloss> 553,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d486fn2">Not printed.</note> (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) 2 plywood
                    items (<gloss target="#t_Deltel1">Deltel</gloss> 557),<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d486fn3">Not printed.</note> and (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) shelled
                    bitter almonds (Para 756) not previously authorized.</p>
                <p>3. On basis approval package deal with Canad, Thorp will (<hi rend="italic"
                        >a</hi>) discuss Austral position with <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss>
                    along lines <gloss target="#t_Deltel1">Deltel</gloss> 568<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d486fn4">March 18, <ref target="#pg_1285">p. 1285</ref>.</note> and
                        (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) discuss UK position with Brit Charge along lines
                    note delivered Younger. In addition he will inform Brit as follows: “That we wld
                    not be willing to proceed with an agreement on basis of present UK offers, and
                    are prepared accept no agreement with UK if our <gloss target="#t_Del1"
                        >Del</gloss> so recommends”.</p>
                <p>4. These discussions scheduled Mar 26. Will inform you substance soonest
                    thereafter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
